    <exercise id="fs-id1569819" type="conceptual-questions">
<problem id="fs-id2458719">
    <para id="import-auto-id2654995">When making an ECG measurement, it is important to measure voltage variations over small time intervals. The time is limited by the <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>RC</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> constant of the circuit—it is not possible to measure time variations shorter than <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontstyle="italic"><m:mrow><m:mtext>RC</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math>. How would you manipulate <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>R</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>C</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> in the circuit to allow the necessary measurements?</para>
