 <para id="import-auto-id3449901">Using the exact exponential treatment, find how much time is required to discharge a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>250-μF</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> capacitor through a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>500-Ω</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> resistor down to 1.00% of its original voltage.</para></problem></exercise>

    <exercise id="fs-id3384990" type="problems-exercises">
<problem id="fs-id2937253">
  <para id="import-auto-id2016933">Using the exact exponential treatment, find how much time is required to charge an initially uncharged 100-pF capacitor through a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>75</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>-M</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">Ω</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> resistor to 90.0% of its final voltage.</para>
    </problem>
<solution id="fs-id3093925">
